{
  "texts": [
    "The SCS-SF demonstrated good internal consistency in the present sample (α Pre = 0.84; α Post = 0.85; α 3-Month Follow-up = 0.85; α 6- Month Follow-up = 0.83).The Brief Resilience Scale (BRS; [106]) is a 6-item measure used to assess psychological resilience.",
    "Specifically, the BRS examines the ability to recover or \"bounce back\" from stressors.",
    "A total score is calculated by averaging responses to the 6 items, resulting in a range of 1 to 5 with higher scores indicating greater psychological resilience.",
    "The BRS has demonstrated good internal consistency (α = 0.80) and expected correlations with psychological distress, wellbeing [106], and psychological flexibility [81].",
    "The BRS demonstrated good to excellent internal consistency in the present sample (α Pre = 0.82; α Post = 0.83; α 3-Month Follow-up = 0.83; α 6-Month Follow-up = 0.85).The Multidimensional Assessment of Interoceptive Awareness-2 (MAIA-2; [107]) is a 37-item measure that assesses interoceptive awareness, or the process by which the nervous system senses, interprets, and integrates signals originating from within the body."
  ]
}